Text.Value: Look, I've already been threatened with death today so, relatively speaking, you seem nice. Can you help me?
You know, killing you is going to be very, very satisfying.
Of course not. It's from an owlbear. But I bet your employers won't know the difference.
Oh, gods no. Please.

EditorData.NodeContext: Insulted/amused that the player thinks you might have had gith friends

Text.Value: Leave.
Oh it certainly looks that way, but inside it is swarming with brutish, stupid, rude githyanki.

EditorData.NodeContext: Again, most offended by the face that they're rude

Text.Value: I'm amazed you escaped the crèche alive, frankly.
Honestly, I was doing them a favour, offering to buy one of their eggs. And how am I repaid? Attacked and run off like some transient.
Leave.
No, it's an owlbear's. I just like it.
I was here on business, before it was blown to Mount Celestia.
Calling it our project seems like a bit of a stretch.
At last. Hta'zith!
So? Where's the egg?
Leave.
A pleasure to do business with you.
Lady, I'm busy. What do you want?
Should you change your mind, you know where to find me.
May I see your wares?
Do you have anything to trade?
And what's this 'good cause', exactly?
Inside that temple is a gith crèche. The githyanki established it in what remained after they slaughtered all of the monks.
I needed a githyanki egg. Contractual business. That blast probably left it as a rather messy scramble.
Well not your eggs specifically, any gith egg...

EditorData.NodeContext: full line "any gith egg would do", but you trail off because you realise the player isn't your enemy

Text.Value: Look over there. Do you see that wretched little hive?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
She points to the Monestary of Lathander, which we can see in the distance

(Direction is forward and to the Expeditioner's right, roughly 2 o'clock)

Text.Value: How... Uncouth. You've rather scuppered a project I was working on.
Acutely observed on both counts.
Who tried to kill you?
...You're not from that crèche, are you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Realising the player isn't your enemy. [YIL-ik]

Text.Value: I suppose there is a reason I'm asking you to do it.
At least we can preserve something of that unfortunate crèche.
An awful proposition that must be disproven once and for all.
And? How much did you offer?
Leave.
They may have chased me away, but surely the gith would welcome a person with such sympathetic views to their crèche.
The best cause there is: knowledge!
I trust that an early payment has ensured swift action. What news of the githyanki egg?
I rather like this plan. You have yourself an accord.
Well, I would advise you work on it in the actual crèche. Dawdling here helps no one.
They believe a githyanki raised in a peaceful, nurturing environment can overcome its violent nature.
All business? Very well, I can respect that.
I said it's a pity you didn't get the egg.
Uh... sure.
A rapscallion I can have grudging respect for. A bare-faced liar, on the other hand...

EditorData.NodeContext: The player just lied to her, but she found them out

Text.Value: Violence is taught, not inherited. You don't need to steal a child to know that.
Please, do enlighten me. What is this 'tradition'?
Perhaps. Explain your plight.
How rude. This is exactly why you people have a bit of a reputation, you know.
Did you have friends in the crèche?
Thank you. Paying upfront seems to have had its benefits.
I was given a task, one surprisingly difficult for someone like me. And yet it would be simplicity itself for you!
The Society believes a githyanki raised in a peaceful, nurturing environment can overcome its violent nature.
Not enough, clearly.
Well, with the right application of force and lift it could be possible...
Now now, no need to get out of humour. Manners are everything.
There's a crèche nearby? Direct me there at once.
My... eggs?
As I was trying to say, this is an entirely benevolent act and all for a very good cause.
The Society of Brilliance supplied me with an ample purse to buy an egg for their studies. Bring me one and that purse is all yours.
No, but this owlbear egg is worth much more. And it can all be yours.
Fortuitous indeed! You shall be rewarded immediately!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character reaches behind back to retrieve item from inventory - hand over is off camera

Text.Value: It's a Lanthaderian monastery - a site of pilgrimage. How is it wretched?
Looks like a monastery to Lathander. What's your problem with the God of the Dawn?
Well, yes, but now we know better. Only some of you are bloodthirsty terrors.
Attack.
You want to steal away our young? Your head is mine for daring to suggest it.
Your charming companion would call it a crèche. But it was built on what remained after the githyanki slaughtered all of the monks. I'd call it a murderous training camp.
A friendly face! Oh you are a sweet, sweet blessing, my dear.
Oh I mean no offence to the Morninglord, I simply prefer when his monasteries aren't overrun with brutish, stupid, rude githyanki.
Happy, are we? Very well, then.
Oh you wonder- hold on.

EditorData.NodeContext: Starts thrilled, saying "oh you wonderful person", but then realises she's not looking at the gith egg she thought she was. This is a different kind of egg.

Text.Value: Fine, but I want payment. Up front.
Some things are in our blood - only a fool would deny that.
What you suggest is revolting. I won't let you do this.
I am not talking to you.
My friend is right: what you suggest is revolting and you need to die.
I'm sure your friend would agree. A githyanki is as likely to forsake its violent nature as a gnome is to fly.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel looks pissed off - scowls & folds her arms

Text.Value: They used to think my people were inherently evil too, you know.
Leave.
I'm not getting involved in this.
Steal one of Gith's own? I will slit your throat for even suggesting it.
The gith that inhabit that crèche of course - stupid, brutish creatures. Not like you at all.
Exactly! I knew you were a learned soul from the moment I set eyes on you.
Such conduct is distasteful. Don't come back without the right egg.

EditorData.NodeContext: The player just lied to her, but she found them out

Text.Value: Do you have any equipment worth trading?
No, but I'd be willing to trade - if you have anything worth trading?
You're right, it does have a rather fabulous sheen. It's surprisingly beautiful.
Look, it's just an egg.
I have the egg - here.
Sorry, who's trying to kill you?
Thank you so much. Do be sure to pop into the Lodge should you ever visit Baldur's Gate.
You've proven an exceptionally efficient friend today. I hope we can work together again.
I have been... less than successful, and if the gith ever see me again, they will kill me. So, I'm asking you to retrieve an egg for me.
What news of our little project? Have you found the egg?
I think you're vile and I'd sooner die than see you get that egg.
But if you believe in this cause so strongly, why not help the society prove your point?
...I beg your pardon?
You've already been generously compensated, so all I have left to offer is my thanks.
You've had one the entire time and didn't say a word?
But I'm not here to seek revenge for the deaths they caused.
My, how fortuitous! Jolly good show cracking through that crèche, they had it guarded up to the gizzard!
Bring me an egg I can deliver to the Society and you will be well rewarded.
Sounds good - I'm in.
Shame that monastery had to go up like that - taking my impeccable reputation for success with it.
Excuse me? Were you not listening? I am on a mission and I will not be stopped by the likes of you or your wretched gith!
Ah. Yes. That.
Pity. You'd have become rather rich had you the proper sense.
No, of course. Not enough blood letting for your taste, I imagine.
I'm working on it.
You know, I've had nothing but trouble all day. I've been accosted, chased, insulted.

EditorData.NodeContext: Lady Esther is especially bothered by the insults

Text.Value: The curves, the colouration, the size - looks right to me.
Did you see that? The entire building - rubble! I bet it took the crèche too. This is a disaster!

EditorData.NodeContext: Upset that your mission to get an egg has been ruined

Text.Value: Brutish and rude by your wretched standards. But stupid? K'chakhi.
The Society of Brilliance believes that it's possible to raise a githyanki to be good.

EditorData.NodeContext: doesn't believe this is possible (is racist)

Text.Value: I need a githyanki egg - which I know may sound a little unsavoury -
Scalabe architecture, good vantage points. Looks empty - perfect ambush spot.
It may look like a peaceful, ruined temple, but it is overrun with brutish, stupid, rude githyanki.

EditorData.NodeContext: Again, most offended by the face that they're rude

Text.Value: You've been sipping from the same goblet as the Society. Perhaps you'd be willing to help, then? To prove your point.
It looks like a temple?
You tried to buy one of their children?
I'm afraid that's not how it works. Egg first - compensation later.
You can't have the egg - I won't support this revolting experiment.
Perhaps you could help me, then? I may not be welcome there, but surely a person with your charm and worldliness could get into the crèche.
Everyone needs a hobby, I suppose. But if you find a gith egg, do return it quickly. No matter how much you 'like' it.
With a pure will and great courage - anyone can rise above their nature.
Punt the egg off the side of the cliff with a hearty kick.

EditorData.logicalname: DARK URGE - HAS EGG - NEAR CLIFF

Text.Value: Why would you want one of their eggs?
Well, you failed to get the egg, so I guess we'll never know.
Now, I believe you have places to be.
Uh huh. And how much will I get?
Oh how fortuitous! And not just because you're not trying to kill me. I was hoping to meet a friendly gith, actually.
You held my success in your hands only to stomp on it, and report it to me with glee? I will not be mocked!
Excellent.
The Society of Brilliance tasked me with acquiring one of their eggs in order to settle a dispute.
Or... fearsome? Pleasantly fearsome?
Hogwash, of course. A githyanki can no more rise above its nature than gnomes can fly.
Violence is taught, not inherited. I would know - I received impeccable training.
And why's that?
A word of advice: avoid direct confrontation. Crèche-bound githyanki can be a deadly sort.
Well, I suppose a spot of conversation never goes amiss. Here's your reward.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character reaches behind back to retrieve item from inventory - hand over is off camera

Text.Value: I want to trade.
*Using every scrap of your concentration, you kick the egg just hard enough that it doesn't crack, but soars like a red dragon.*
I know! They were pure savages - not like you. I'm sure you would appreciate that this is all in the name of knowledge.
In fact, maybe you'd be able to succeed where I... was less successful.

EditorData.NodeContext: doesn't want to say "where I failed"

Text.Value: I should hope so! When adventure calls, I am always thoroughly prepared. Take a look.
Nod your head, play along. Find out what you can, take her head when it's done.
I left your stupid crèche, why are you still chasing me? I don't even want your bloody eggs!
You - you're not from the crèche? Oh, how fortuitous! And not just because you're not trying to kill me.
Inside that temple lies one of your 'crèches', which I gather has its very own hatchery, presumably chock full of eggs.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
She points to the Monestary of Lathander, which we can see in the distance

(Direction is forward and to the Expeditioner's right, roughly 2 o'clock)

Text.Value: Leave.
I might have a few trinkets worth a glance.
A reward is most assuredly in order.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character reaches behind back to retrieve item from inventory - hand over is off camera

Text.Value: Why did you want a githyanki egg?
Trusting you with payment up front was a good investment, it seems.
I blew it up. The crèche too.
Alas, I shall have to search for that egg elsewhere now.
Calm yourself, I am not chasing you.
I need a githyanki egg - which may sound a little unsavoury, but I swear this is all for an excellent cause.
Stop there! Not one step further!

EditorData.NodeContext: First sentence partly under her breath to herself; second sentence loudly and somewhat patronising, as if she doesn't quite expect the player to understand the language

Text.Value: How did you know there was a crèche in there?
Why exactly do you want this egg?
What makes you think I'm friendly?
To settle a debate. Nature or nurture.
I would be happy to reveal its extremely secret location if you'd be willing to perform one small favour for me.
I have the egg right here. Take it.
It looks different to what I expected. Are you sure that's a gith egg?
It's for the Society of Brilliance. Clever lot, but they're convinced they can raise a githyanki child to be good.
The Society of Brilliance asked me to acquire one of their roe so they can incubate it and, once it hatches, raise the spawn in their tradition.
I knew I was right about you beasts.
And once inside, you could simply... purloin an egg.
What? Surrender an egg, and I will not stand for it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shocked that player is willing to go along with stealing a gith egg

Text.Value: I'm sorry? You think you can take my money and then just back out? I will not be robbed by the likes of you!
You're in luck - I've got the githyanki egg you were looking for.
What the Society doesn't know won't hurt it, and we're left handsomely legacied either way.
Have you given any more thought to the retrieval of that githyanki egg?
What a creative solution. I hope we can work together again some day.
I - uh - it's simply because you look so... pleasant.
I already have an egg - here.
...Look, I just need someone to fetch me a gith egg. Can you do that?
Here's your payment. I'd hope it's enough to warrant your discretion too.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character reaches behind back to retrieve item from inventory - hand over is off camera

Text.Value: I have your egg. Take it.
I found an egg, but destroyed it.
How excellent. Here is, as promised, your reward.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character reaches behind back to retrieve item from inventory - hand over is off camera

Text.Value: A flying gnome. I'd need an airfoil, of course. And a source of propulsion.
You'll be well compensated, of course. Just bring me an egg.
So. What do you say?
You brute, what have you done? You will pay for this!
They have the audacity to call that hole a crèche, as if it weren't actually a murderous training camp.
Very well, here's the money. Now I expect a speedy delivery.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Character reaches behind back to retrieve item from inventory - hand over is off camera

Text.Value: Shka'keth! You would steal away one of our children?
Hmm? Oh. Nothing.
The Society of Brilliance have asked me to acquire one of your people's roe so they can incubate it and, once it hatches, raise it in their tradition.
State your cause. I'll be the judge of how 'good' it is.
Very well, but I'll make note of how much time you waste trawling through baubles.
I see this being a highly prosperous partnership.
Produce the owlbear egg.
What? No, of course not! I was merely - well...
This could be an auspicious meeting, come to think of it. I was hoping to meet a friendly gith.

Synopsis: An aging expeditioner gives the player the task of collecting a githyanki egg and debates nature vs. nurture.
